review_blob: 750ml bottle, 2010 Vintage. Red-amber color. Aroma is fruity vinegar notes. Taste is amazingly balanced sourness.
355ml bottle from 2012. Color is black as night with almost no head. Aroma is bourbon bourbon bourbon... Taste is dark chocolate, roasted, boozy, cherries.
500ml bottle from Systembolaget. Pours dark copper. Aroma is nutty and malty. Taste is fruity and slightly roasted. Great christmas beer
250ml bottle. Black in color and a small dark head. Aroma is whiskey, a bit to much. Taste whiskey, roasted malt and chocolate. A bit disappointing...
beer_name: Nynshamns Sotholmen Extra Stout Svensk Ek

review_blob: 330ml bottle from 2011. Pours dark with very little foam. Amazing smell, spices. Tastes malty with a lot of raisins, spices and dark sugars. A truly amazing beer!
Huge amount of coffee is the first thing that you smell. And same with the taste, coffee and a slight heat. And a smooth chocolate finish. Tasteful beer that suppress the abv very well.
